track_notes:
Bike from Melchsee-Frutt to “Schnuer”, then following the red (and later blue) marked hiking trail to Barglen. Difficulty T4+ (I) on SAC scale. The section that goes around the north side of Chli Hohmad can be difficult if snow/ice is present, and may then require ice axe + crampons to negotiate safely. Note that the descent in this track was by abseiling (3x25 m, 60m rope recommended) down the south face from Barglenchäle.

In summer, you can drive to Melchsee-Frutt by car (CHF 25 fee). Traffic on the toll road is uphill during even hours, and downhill during odd hours - make sure you arrive/depart at the right time to avoid a long wait.
track_title: Round trip with bike and abseiling
